This paper deals with the design of auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The focus is on multi-unit auctions, which involve multiple identical items being sold simultaneously, and the paper proposes prior-free auctions with constant-factor approximation guarantees. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as these fields often involve the design and analysis of algorithms with performance guarantees. Finally, the paper compares the expected revenue of the proposed auctions to a benchmark based on monotone prices, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG), as this field often involves the development of models that optimize some objective function.
